 }}
</ref>

The USDA has issued recalls of beef supplies that involved introduction of [[downer (animal)|downer cow]]s into the food supply. [[Hallmark/Westland Meat Packing Company]] was found to have used electric shocks to prod downer cows into the slaughtering system in 2007.<ref>{{cite news
 | title = Meat Recalls to Name Retailers
